1
00:00:05,733 --> 00:00:06,700
<i> Jobert!</i>

2
00:00:07,833 --> 00:00:09,267
<i> Jobert! Jobert!</i>

3
00:00:09,400 --> 00:00:11,100
<i> What happened? He's bleeding!</i>

4
00:00:11,233 --> 00:00:12,833
<i>We can't determine
what exactly happened.</i>

5
00:00:12,967 --> 00:00:15,100
<i>We found him already
at the bottom of the stairs.</i>

6
00:00:15,233 --> 00:00:17,733
<i>These are the patient's
valuables and clothes.</i>

7
00:00:17,867 --> 00:00:19,067
<i> I'll take care of it.</i>

8
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:21,467
<i>Why did he go to that part
of the mansion?</i>

9
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:23,267
<i> He's afraid of the dark.</i>

10
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:25,233
<i>We can't let that video
see the light of day.</i>

11
00:00:25,367 --> 00:00:27,000
<i>Thea?
What are you looking for here?</i>

12
00:00:27,133 --> 00:00:28,367
<i> This is a cell phone, right?</i>

13
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:29,700
<i> Why is this here?</i>

14
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:32,700
<i> Jobert! Jobert, wake up!</i>

15
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:18,367
Jobert!

16
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:20,500
Jobert!

17
00:01:21,600 --> 00:01:23,833
Jobert!

18
00:01:23,967 --> 00:01:25,500
Jobert!

19
00:01:25,633 --> 00:01:27,600
Jobert!

20
00:01:27,733 --> 00:01:30,333
Big Sister is here, Jobert!
Jobert!

21
00:01:30,467 --> 00:01:32,167
Wake up! No, wait!

22
00:01:32,300 --> 00:01:34,467
I haven't talked to him yet!
Just a moment!

23
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:35,767
Jobert!

24
00:01:37,033 --> 00:01:39,467
You told me
he fell down the stairs!

25
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:40,667
I thought it was just fractures.

26
00:01:40,833 --> 00:01:42,300
Why is it like this?
He's bleeding?

27
00:01:44,867 --> 00:01:46,833
No one saw
what exactly happened.

28
00:01:46,967 --> 00:01:49,633
We found him already
at the bottom of the stairs.

29
00:01:52,033 --> 00:01:52,967
Marj! Marj!

30
00:01:54,700 --> 00:01:55,800
[STAMMERING]

31
00:01:55,933 --> 00:01:58,033
I was just talking to him
earlier.

32
00:01:58,167 --> 00:02:01,067
He told me to take care
of Jasmine and myself.

33
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:02,700
And then this happened.

34
00:02:02,833 --> 00:02:05,400
Why did this happen?

35
00:02:05,533 --> 00:02:07,533
He'll be okay, right?

36
00:02:07,667 --> 00:02:08,400
Tell me...

37
00:02:08,533 --> 00:02:10,433
he'll be okay?

38
00:02:11,467 --> 00:02:13,033
<i> Kind Brother!</i>

39
00:02:19,967 --> 00:02:22,233
Marj, it was just an accident.

40
00:02:22,367 --> 00:02:23,267
But it's my fault.

41
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:26,133
I didn't prevent
what was supposed to happen.

42
00:02:26,267 --> 00:02:29,767
Marj, I'm so sorry.
I'm so sorry.

43
00:02:29,900 --> 00:02:33,633
If there's anyone to blame here,
it's me.

44
00:02:33,767 --> 00:02:37,733
I wish I hadn't left him.
This wouldn't have happened.

45
00:02:37,867 --> 00:02:39,700
[SOBBING]

46
00:02:39,833 --> 00:02:41,867
I was such a careless sister.

47
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,833
[SOBBING]

48
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:50,467
All right, Paolo.

49
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:52,333
Update me immediately

50
00:02:52,467 --> 00:02:55,067
as soon as you hear
from Jobert's doctor, okay?

51
00:02:56,567 --> 00:02:58,533
Okay, then. Bye.

52
00:02:58,667 --> 00:02:59,900
Greg...

53
00:03:00,033 --> 00:03:05,700
aren't we forgetting to invite
someone to our renewal of vows?

54
00:03:05,833 --> 00:03:06,867
Oh, right.

55
00:03:07,100 --> 00:03:10,533
Please remind your friends that
they can bring a plus one.

56
00:03:10,667 --> 00:03:12,967
But only the legal ones, okay?

57
00:03:13,100 --> 00:03:15,667
Because I don't want an
infestation of mistresses

58
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:17,600
on our special day.

59
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:23,500
Are you really
that out of touch, Regina?

60
00:03:25,167 --> 00:03:27,700
There was an accident
in our home.

61
00:03:27,833 --> 00:03:29,500
And yet,

62
00:03:29,633 --> 00:03:31,433
this is still
what you're focused on.

63
00:03:32,933 --> 00:03:35,100
But what am I supposed to do?

64
00:03:35,233 --> 00:03:38,600
Just drop everything
because there was an accident?

65
00:03:38,733 --> 00:03:42,467
It's not my fault that
Jobert is clumsy and stupid.

66
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:44,200
But you know
who's really to blame,

67
00:03:44,333 --> 00:03:46,167
his flirtatious mother Evelyn.

68
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:48,467
Because if Evelyn was as good at
parenting

69
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:51,733
as she is at stealing someone
else's husband,

70
00:03:51,867 --> 00:03:54,067
her child
wouldn't have gotten hurt.

71
00:03:56,733 --> 00:04:00,133
I think we should postpone
the renewal of vows for now.

72
00:04:00,467 --> 00:04:03,333
It doesn't look good that...

73
00:04:03,467 --> 00:04:06,233
we're celebrating

74
00:04:06,367 --> 00:04:09,167
while Jasmine and Jobert
are in the hospital.

75
00:04:09,300 --> 00:04:11,667
The patient suffered severe
swelling in the brain

76
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:13,133
due to the accident.

77
00:04:13,267 --> 00:04:16,667
And we had to perform
a decompressive craniectomy

78
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:18,833
to reduce the pressure
in his brain

79
00:04:18,967 --> 00:04:22,067
and to avoid
further brain damage.

80
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:27,333
He is currently in a deep coma
and is completely unresponsive.

81
00:04:29,167 --> 00:04:31,300
How long will
he be like this?

82
00:04:31,433 --> 00:04:33,500
Is there still hope
that he'll wake up?

83
00:04:33,633 --> 00:04:35,733
Is there anything we can do?

84
00:04:35,867 --> 00:04:38,333
We have to keep him here
in the ICU.

85
00:04:38,467 --> 00:04:41,900
We have to monitor him closely.

86
00:04:42,033 --> 00:04:43,100
And once he stabilizes,

87
00:04:43,233 --> 00:04:45,900
we can transfer him
to a regular room.

88
00:04:46,033 --> 00:04:47,700
But at this stage,

89
00:04:47,833 --> 00:04:53,067
we really can't say
if he will regain consciousness.

90
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:56,233
But for now,
we just have to wait and see.

91
00:04:58,567 --> 00:04:59,867
Excuse me.

92
00:05:11,467 --> 00:05:14,867
Oh, Greg.

93
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:17,667
Oh, my dear Greg.

94
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:22,767
Did you suddenly grow a halo?

95
00:05:25,067 --> 00:05:26,333
Too bad.

96
00:05:26,467 --> 00:05:29,167
It looks incredibly fake on you.

97
00:05:30,900 --> 00:05:33,900
Don't you dare use
Jasmine and Jobert as an excuse

98
00:05:34,067 --> 00:05:36,200
to cancel our renewal of vows.

99
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:42,833
Because you might be forgetting,
we have an agreement.

100
00:05:42,967 --> 00:05:45,900
And if you don't comply
with my demands,

101
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:51,300
I'll serve on a silver platter

102
00:05:51,433 --> 00:05:55,533
all your dirty little secrets
for the world to see.

103
00:05:59,967 --> 00:06:03,600
I don't think you want things
to get messy, do you?

104
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,200
Jobert...

105
00:06:22,167 --> 00:06:23,967
forgive me.

106
00:06:25,967 --> 00:06:30,133
I know I told you I would
do everything to keep you safe.

107
00:06:31,533 --> 00:06:33,733
I'm sorry
if Big Sister failed you.

108
00:06:34,767 --> 00:06:36,700
I didn't protect you.

109
00:06:38,700 --> 00:06:40,867
Jobert, I promise...

110
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:43,500
I'll find Mom.

111
00:06:43,667 --> 00:06:46,167
And when you wake up,

112
00:06:46,300 --> 00:06:49,167
we'll all be together again.

113
00:06:49,300 --> 00:06:50,667
Wake up.

114
00:06:53,167 --> 00:06:56,133
Don't leave me, Jobert.

115
00:06:56,267 --> 00:07:03,167
[SOBBING]

116
00:07:03,300 --> 00:07:06,300
[SPEAKS IN VISAYAN LANGUAGE]

117
00:07:06,433 --> 00:07:16,400
[SOBBING]

118
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:24,067
Marj.

119
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:25,600
Marj.

120
00:07:25,733 --> 00:07:28,933
Jobert is already out
of the ICU.

121
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:31,800
- How is he?
- Still comatose.

122
00:07:31,933 --> 00:07:33,500
No development yet.

123
00:07:35,767 --> 00:07:37,067
Just hang in there.

124
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:45,233
Love, how's Jasmine?

125
00:07:45,367 --> 00:07:47,133
Don't worry about
our daughter.

126
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:50,467
I'll take care of her.
I won't abandon her.

127
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:52,367
Doesn't she have chemo infusion
later?

128
00:07:54,900 --> 00:07:57,133
Thank you
for watching over her.

129
00:07:58,367 --> 00:08:01,133
I don't know
how to split myself.

130
00:08:01,267 --> 00:08:04,600
As much as I want to be there
for our daughter,

131
00:08:04,733 --> 00:08:08,067
I feel like I can't leave
Jobert.

132
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:11,433
It feels like something worse
might happen to him.

133
00:08:11,567 --> 00:08:14,033
Don't think like that.

134
00:08:14,167 --> 00:08:17,667
Ma'am, Sir, here are the
patient's valuables and clothes.

135
00:08:19,700 --> 00:08:21,900
Why are these being turned over
only now?

136
00:08:22,067 --> 00:08:23,433
Sorry, there was a delay.

137
00:08:23,567 --> 00:08:25,267
I left instructions with my
coworker while I was on leave,

138
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:28,433
but they didn't take care of it.

139
00:08:28,567 --> 00:08:30,100
I'll take care of it.

140
00:08:31,367 --> 00:08:33,000
Thank you.

141
00:08:39,900 --> 00:08:41,400
Love?

142
00:08:42,433 --> 00:08:44,333
Are you okay?

143
00:08:44,467 --> 00:08:46,567
Yeah.

144
00:08:46,700 --> 00:08:48,000
I just checked
because it looked like...

145
00:08:48,133 --> 00:08:50,367
the nurse was going through
Jobert's things.

146
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,867
Just place them
on that table.

147
00:09:00,567 --> 00:09:02,800
What?
Did you see the cell phone?

148
00:09:02,933 --> 00:09:04,633
It's not among Jobert's things.

149
00:09:04,767 --> 00:09:06,033
Are you sure?

150
00:09:06,167 --> 00:09:07,867
Yes, I already checked
his belongings.

151
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:10,333
I didn't
find a cell phone.

152
00:09:10,467 --> 00:09:12,367
Maybe Marj already found it.

153
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:15,533
Wait, check her bag.
It might be there.

154
00:09:15,667 --> 00:09:17,567
I just can't go through
her things like that.

155
00:09:17,700 --> 00:09:19,500
Do you want her to start
wondering and asking questions?

156
00:09:19,633 --> 00:09:21,500
Just...

157
00:09:21,633 --> 00:09:24,533
don't stop looking for it.

158
00:09:24,667 --> 00:09:26,200
I'll also look in the garden.

159
00:09:26,333 --> 00:09:28,667
It might have just fallen there.

160
00:09:28,833 --> 00:09:31,400
Just let me know
if you find anything.

161
00:09:31,533 --> 00:09:33,800
We can't let that video
see the light of day.

162
00:09:33,933 --> 00:09:38,800
And if that happens,
my wife will never forgive me.

163
00:09:38,933 --> 00:09:42,100
Our families will be destroyed.
Do you understand?

164
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,100
Then I saw Uncle Jobert.

165
00:09:57,233 --> 00:09:58,533
He was already covered in blood.

166
00:10:00,133 --> 00:10:03,400
It was my first time
seeing something like that.

167
00:10:03,567 --> 00:10:06,100
I'm sorry you had to see
your uncle like that.

168
00:10:06,233 --> 00:10:08,800
But don't worry too much.

169
00:10:09,067 --> 00:10:11,900
I'm sure he's being treated
at the hospital.

170
00:10:12,033 --> 00:10:14,733
But what if they can't save him?

171
00:10:14,867 --> 00:10:17,500
I won't be able to forgive
myself then.

172
00:10:19,700 --> 00:10:23,167
Maybe if I hadn't left him
that night,

173
00:10:23,300 --> 00:10:25,400
then maybe I could have
prevented it, right?

174
00:10:25,533 --> 00:10:26,933
Don't blame yourself.

175
00:10:27,067 --> 00:10:28,933
It was an accident.

176
00:10:29,067 --> 00:10:31,800
You didn't mean
for it to happen.

177
00:10:31,933 --> 00:10:34,200
But still, Xander, what...

178
00:10:49,333 --> 00:10:51,167
Don't think about that, okay?

179
00:10:52,533 --> 00:10:54,533
It's not your fault.

180
00:10:54,667 --> 00:10:56,933
And no one blames
you for what you did.

181
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:03,833
Sorry.

182
00:11:03,967 --> 00:11:07,067
I forgot that Mom asked me
to do something.

183
00:11:08,433 --> 00:11:10,633
I have to go now. I'm sorry.

184
00:11:10,767 --> 00:11:12,300
- [SNIFFLES]
- Okay.

185
00:11:12,433 --> 00:11:21,633
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

186
00:11:24,500 --> 00:11:27,267
How did the treatment go?

187
00:11:29,733 --> 00:11:31,833
It went smoothly.

188
00:11:31,967 --> 00:11:34,700
But before she fell asleep,

189
00:11:34,833 --> 00:11:38,267
she kept asking
about her Uncle Jobert.

190
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:40,300
She's really worried.

191
00:11:42,967 --> 00:11:44,933
Love...

192
00:11:45,067 --> 00:11:47,267
maybe you should go home first
and get some rest.

193
00:11:49,167 --> 00:11:52,067
I'll have Yolly watch over
Jobert for now.

194
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:55,433
You've been exhausted for days
and not sleeping.

195
00:11:55,567 --> 00:11:59,033
You might end up collapsing
yourself.

196
00:11:59,167 --> 00:12:03,133
I also can't sleep
when I go home.

197
00:12:03,267 --> 00:12:04,633
Every time I close my eyes,

198
00:12:04,767 --> 00:12:08,433
I imagine what happened
to Jobert.

199
00:12:08,567 --> 00:12:10,000
How did he fall?

200
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:15,600
We know my brother is playful,
but he's careful.

201
00:12:15,767 --> 00:12:18,900
He knows where he can
play and where it's not allowed.

202
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:24,433
Marj, accidents happen.

203
00:12:24,567 --> 00:12:26,300
Even if we're very careful.

204
00:12:28,767 --> 00:12:31,300
But why there?

205
00:12:31,433 --> 00:12:33,700
Why did he go
to that part of the mansion?

206
00:12:33,833 --> 00:12:35,767
At the garden?

207
00:12:35,900 --> 00:12:38,300
I mean,
he's never been there before.

208
00:12:38,433 --> 00:12:40,133
And it's dark there, Love.

209
00:12:40,267 --> 00:12:42,100
He's afraid of the dark.

210
00:12:44,533 --> 00:12:46,200
I keep thinking maybe...

211
00:12:46,333 --> 00:12:48,367
maybe he was looking
for something.

212
00:12:48,533 --> 00:12:50,233
Or maybe
he was following someone.

213
00:12:51,667 --> 00:12:54,767
He wouldn't just go there
without a reason.

214
00:12:58,033 --> 00:13:01,267
Did you hear Ashley scream?

215
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:03,733
Where were you then?

216
00:13:03,867 --> 00:13:05,833
I mean, when you told me
you were going home

217
00:13:05,967 --> 00:13:08,133
because you had something
to fix.

218
00:13:08,267 --> 00:13:09,800
What was that, love?

219
00:13:09,933 --> 00:13:13,000
[STAMMERING]

220
00:13:13,133 --> 00:13:18,467
I told Dad
I'd take a leave from work...

221
00:13:19,933 --> 00:13:23,033
while Jasmine
goes through chemo.

222
00:13:24,500 --> 00:13:27,667
It's time for me
to step up as a father.

223
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:30,767
I'll be the one
to watch over Jasmine

224
00:13:30,900 --> 00:13:32,333
so you can focus on Jobert.

225
00:13:33,433 --> 00:13:35,767
You had to go home
just to say that?

226
00:13:35,900 --> 00:13:37,600
[CHUCKLES] Come on.

227
00:13:37,733 --> 00:13:39,500
You know Dad, right?

228
00:13:39,633 --> 00:13:41,500
He wouldn't take you seriously

229
00:13:41,633 --> 00:13:44,967
unless you talked to him
properly.

230
00:13:45,100 --> 00:13:46,767
Why, Love?

231
00:13:46,900 --> 00:13:48,733
Don't you believe me?

232
00:13:50,100 --> 00:13:52,567
Of course, I believe you.

233
00:13:52,700 --> 00:13:56,367
It's just weird
how the timing lines up.

234
00:13:56,533 --> 00:13:58,133
It feels like ***

235
00:13:58,267 --> 00:14:01,800
First it was Jasmine,
then Jobert.

236
00:14:01,933 --> 00:14:06,000
I feel like there's something
I'm not seeing.

237
00:14:06,133 --> 00:14:08,067
Love...

238
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:10,000
you're just exhausted.

239
00:14:10,133 --> 00:14:12,400
Don't think about
all sorts of things.

240
00:14:14,300 --> 00:14:15,800
Just...

241
00:14:15,933 --> 00:14:18,067
whatever happens,

242
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:19,933
I'm here.

243
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:22,367
We'll do this together.

244
00:14:22,500 --> 00:14:24,867
And I will never leave you,
okay?

245
00:14:26,067 --> 00:14:30,333
[INTENSE MUSIC]

246
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:34,567
Oh dear, Ma'am Marj's problems
never seem to end.

247
00:14:34,700 --> 00:14:36,567
It's pitiful.

248
00:14:36,700 --> 00:14:39,667
That's true. It's terrible, one
after another, her misfortunes.

249
00:14:39,800 --> 00:14:44,333
If things get worse, she herself
might collapse one day.

250
00:14:44,467 --> 00:14:46,900
Hey, don't say that.

251
00:14:47,033 --> 00:14:49,233
Because if that happens,
the children will suffer.

252
00:14:49,367 --> 00:14:51,567
Jobert and Jasmine.

253
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:57,667
Oh, are you okay?

254
00:14:57,800 --> 00:15:01,133
I've been noticing for a while
how quiet you've been.

255
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:06,267
And, aren't you affected by
what's happening to Ma'am Marj?

256
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:08,933
Why should I let myself
be affected?

257
00:15:10,833 --> 00:15:11,800
I no longer care

258
00:15:11,933 --> 00:15:14,667
about what's happening
to the people living here.

259
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:16,700
If it were up to me,

260
00:15:16,833 --> 00:15:19,067
they could all burn in hell.

261
00:15:20,533 --> 00:15:22,800
Oh my. Oh my!

262
00:15:24,500 --> 00:15:28,133
Why do you seem so angry?

263
00:15:28,267 --> 00:15:29,433
Aren't you the one

264
00:15:29,567 --> 00:15:31,500
who's been living here
in the mansion for years?

265
00:15:31,633 --> 00:15:33,833
You should be
more concerned.

266
00:15:33,967 --> 00:15:36,667
Since you already considered
them family.

267
00:15:36,833 --> 00:15:39,467
[HUFFS]

268
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:41,400
Family?

269
00:15:42,867 --> 00:15:44,700
You call them family, Oscar?

270
00:15:44,833 --> 00:15:45,933
[HUFFS]

271
00:15:46,067 --> 00:15:49,367
Hey, let's not fool ourselves.

272
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:52,733
When did they ever
treat us like family?

273
00:15:54,567 --> 00:15:56,033
Servants.

274
00:15:56,167 --> 00:15:57,900
Slaves.

275
00:15:58,033 --> 00:16:00,267
That's all we are to them.

276
00:16:01,767 --> 00:16:03,800
So, why should I pretend

277
00:16:03,933 --> 00:16:07,333
to care about what's happening
to them in this house?

278
00:16:07,467 --> 00:16:08,700
Hey!

279
00:16:08,867 --> 00:16:10,733
And I won't stay here
much longer.

280
00:16:10,867 --> 00:16:13,200
What do you mean?

281
00:16:13,333 --> 00:16:15,200
Just one more month
and I'm gone.

282
00:16:15,333 --> 00:16:17,167
I'm resigning.

283
00:16:17,300 --> 00:16:19,733
- Seriously?
- What do you mean?

284
00:16:25,933 --> 00:16:29,567
The doctor said if his condition
stays like this,

285
00:16:29,700 --> 00:16:34,833
there's a higher chance
that he might not recover.

286
00:16:34,967 --> 00:16:36,267
Marj...

287
00:16:37,733 --> 00:16:39,700
don't lose hope.

288
00:16:42,100 --> 00:16:43,767
You need to fight
for your brother.

289
00:16:43,900 --> 00:16:51,267
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

290
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:52,867
What is it, Jobert?

291
00:16:54,800 --> 00:16:56,833
You don't want to see
your sister crying?

292
00:16:56,967 --> 00:17:02,700
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

293
00:17:02,833 --> 00:17:06,033
Jobert told me not to worry.

294
00:17:07,833 --> 00:17:09,567
He said he'll fight.

295
00:17:09,700 --> 00:17:11,167
He won't give up.

296
00:17:12,900 --> 00:17:14,333
Thank you.

297
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:21,433
I'm trying to be strong,
but sometimes it's exhausting.

298
00:17:23,100 --> 00:17:27,533
I wish my mom were here
to be with me.

299
00:17:27,667 --> 00:17:29,933
And it really feels like...

300
00:17:30,067 --> 00:17:33,633
just hearing my mom's voice
is what he needs

301
00:17:33,767 --> 00:17:36,067
to wake up and recover.

302
00:17:39,833 --> 00:17:41,300
Don't worry.

303
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:44,967
I'll look for your mom.

304
00:17:45,100 --> 00:17:48,567
Thank you so much, Edward,
but you don't have to do that.

305
00:17:48,733 --> 00:17:51,367
- It's already too much trouble.
- No, no, no.

306
00:17:51,500 --> 00:17:54,167
Marj, Marj, I want to help.

307
00:17:54,300 --> 00:17:55,833
I want to help you.

308
00:17:57,700 --> 00:18:02,400
I don't want to see you
like this or struggling.

309
00:18:02,533 --> 00:18:05,367
And if your mom is the way...

310
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:08,600
to lighten the burden
you're carrying,

311
00:18:10,267 --> 00:18:11,800
that's what I'm going to do.
I'll do it.

312
00:18:15,700 --> 00:18:18,000
Just trust me on this.

313
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:25,900
[INTENSE MUSIC]

314
00:18:26,033 --> 00:18:27,867
Where could it be?

315
00:18:29,767 --> 00:18:32,100
It must be around here
somewhere.

316
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:35,233
Damn it, that Jobert.

317
00:18:35,367 --> 00:18:37,433
He didn't even die.

318
00:18:37,567 --> 00:18:39,367
He even left us
with more problems.

319
00:18:39,500 --> 00:18:49,467
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

320
00:18:52,433 --> 00:18:53,467
Thea?

321
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:59,567
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

322
00:18:59,733 --> 00:19:01,033
What are you looking for here?

323
00:19:02,667 --> 00:19:04,600
[STAMMERS]

324
00:19:04,733 --> 00:19:07,133
I'm looking for my earrings.

325
00:19:07,267 --> 00:19:09,000
I think they fell here.

326
00:19:09,133 --> 00:19:09,933
[STAMMERS]

327
00:19:10,067 --> 00:19:12,033
They're my favorite.

328
00:19:12,167 --> 00:19:14,367
They can't go missing.

329
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:16,733
Where are they?

330
00:19:16,867 --> 00:19:19,500
How did your earrings end up
here?

331
00:19:19,633 --> 00:19:21,567
What were you doing
in this spot?

332
00:19:23,567 --> 00:19:25,500
Well,

333
00:19:25,633 --> 00:19:27,733
the signal inside was weak,

334
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:30,567
so I went out
to get better reception.

335
00:19:33,700 --> 00:19:36,333
- But how...
- Wait.

336
00:19:36,467 --> 00:19:38,700
Why are you asking
so many questions?

337
00:19:38,833 --> 00:19:40,433
Shouldn't you be the one
explaining to me

338
00:19:40,567 --> 00:19:42,667
why you only got home now?

339
00:19:42,800 --> 00:19:44,500
Where did you come from?

340
00:19:44,633 --> 00:19:47,933
I just stopped by the hospital
to check on Jobert and Jasmine.

341
00:19:50,333 --> 00:19:52,667
Were they really the ones
you visited,

342
00:19:52,800 --> 00:19:54,667
or did you really just want
to see Marj?

343
00:19:54,800 --> 00:19:55,600
[SCOFFS]

344
00:19:55,733 --> 00:19:57,033
Come on.

345
00:19:57,167 --> 00:19:59,733
Don't put malice into that.

346
00:19:59,867 --> 00:20:01,967
Then why are you defensive?

347
00:20:02,133 --> 00:20:04,533
You know, if you don't want me
meddling in your life,

348
00:20:04,667 --> 00:20:06,733
don't meddle in mine!

349
00:20:31,433 --> 00:20:36,333
The doctor said you can't feel
anything because your in coma.

350
00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:42,233
I hope it's true because you
have too much bruises.

351
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:50,067
It's better to see you sleeping
rather than suffering in pain.

352
00:20:53,300 --> 00:20:55,800
But, Jobert, please...

353
00:20:55,933 --> 00:20:57,767
Please, wake up now.

354
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:02,333
Wake up.

355
00:21:02,467 --> 00:21:12,433
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

356
00:21:13,633 --> 00:21:14,767
Jobert?

357
00:21:14,900 --> 00:21:16,500
Jobert, wake up.

358
00:21:16,633 --> 00:21:17,600
Jobert.

359
00:21:17,733 --> 00:21:19,967
Doctor!

360
00:21:28,600 --> 00:21:29,900
Come on, Pong.

361
00:21:31,100 --> 00:21:32,867
Here you go, Pong.

362
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:35,300
Eat this.

363
00:21:35,433 --> 00:21:38,833
You still don't want to eat,
Pong.

364
00:21:38,967 --> 00:21:41,300
You probably miss Uncle Jobert.

365
00:21:43,333 --> 00:21:47,433
I also miss my best friend, Jas.

366
00:21:47,567 --> 00:21:50,467
Maybe Pong will eat

367
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:52,467
if he's beside Uncle Jobert.

368
00:21:52,600 --> 00:21:54,033
Don't worry...

369
00:21:54,167 --> 00:21:56,867
I'll bring Pong later to the
hospital when I come back.

370
00:21:58,867 --> 00:22:01,500
Thanks, Dad.

371
00:22:01,633 --> 00:22:03,533
I'm sure...

372
00:22:03,667 --> 00:22:05,600
Uncle Jobert would love that.

373
00:22:08,467 --> 00:22:12,033
Daughter, how are you?

374
00:22:12,167 --> 00:22:13,733
Are you okay?

375
00:22:13,867 --> 00:22:17,500
I still see
the image of Uncle Jobert

376
00:22:17,667 --> 00:22:19,667
lying at the bottom
of the stairs.

377
00:22:19,800 --> 00:22:22,533
Daughter, do you want to talk
about it?

378
00:22:22,667 --> 00:22:23,833
I'm all ears.

379
00:22:23,967 --> 00:22:25,433
I'll listen to you.

380
00:22:25,567 --> 00:22:26,600
You're here, Dad.

381
00:22:28,033 --> 00:22:32,933
That's enough for me.

382
00:22:33,067 --> 00:22:36,067
I just miss our bonding moments.

383
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:40,600
Like what we used to have
in Cebu.

384
00:22:40,733 --> 00:22:44,500
But everyone in the house...

385
00:22:44,633 --> 00:22:46,233
seems full of problems.

386
00:22:47,867 --> 00:22:49,333
It's so toxic.

387
00:22:50,833 --> 00:22:54,300
It feels like there are no
reasons to have fun.

388
00:22:54,433 --> 00:22:57,500
I understand how you feel.

389
00:22:57,633 --> 00:22:59,833
You want to be sensitive
to what's happening around you,

390
00:22:59,967 --> 00:23:01,733
and that's valid.

391
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:06,867
But just because there are
issues and problems

392
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:10,233
with the people in this house,
it doesn't mean life stops.

393
00:23:11,367 --> 00:23:16,700
You know, sometimes it's okay
to allow yourself to be happy.

394
00:23:16,833 --> 00:23:18,600
And...

395
00:23:18,733 --> 00:23:22,200
it's also okay not to feel good.

396
00:23:22,367 --> 00:23:23,633
That's normal, my child.

397
00:23:25,367 --> 00:23:28,133
Just always remember,
Dad is here.

398
00:23:28,267 --> 00:23:29,733
Whatever happens,

399
00:23:29,867 --> 00:23:32,867
whatever you feel,
whatever you want to say,

400
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:35,400
I'm here.
I'm always here for you.

401
00:23:37,300 --> 00:23:38,633
Thank you, Dad.

402
00:23:40,600 --> 00:23:41,767
I love you, my child.

403
00:23:41,900 --> 00:23:43,367
I love you too, Dad.

404
00:23:45,833 --> 00:23:50,667
Doctor, I swear.
I saw my brother's finger move.

405
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:52,733
It is possible that what you saw

406
00:23:52,867 --> 00:23:55,300
was reflex activity
from his body.

407
00:23:55,467 --> 00:23:56,433
It can happen.

408
00:23:56,567 --> 00:24:00,567
But even if his brain
isn't conscious.

409
00:24:00,700 --> 00:24:02,967
Doesn't that mean
that it's a sign

410
00:24:03,100 --> 00:24:05,033
that he might be close
to waking up?

411
00:24:05,167 --> 00:24:08,367
Mrs. Torrecampo, I don't want
to crush your hope,

412
00:24:08,500 --> 00:24:12,200
but the longer your brother
stays in a coma,

413
00:24:12,333 --> 00:24:13,400
the greater the risk

414
00:24:13,533 --> 00:24:15,800
that this could lead to a
permanent vegetative state.

415
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:22,900
Are you saying that he might
never wake up ever?

416
00:24:23,033 --> 00:24:24,267
I'm sorry.

417
00:24:24,400 --> 00:24:34,367
[INTENSE MUSIC]

418
00:24:39,100 --> 00:24:43,533
I didn't know what you like
that would cheer you up, so...

419
00:24:43,667 --> 00:24:44,433
I got you this.

420
00:24:46,133 --> 00:24:48,133
Oh, thanks.

421
00:24:48,267 --> 00:24:50,533
But it's not my birthday today.

422
00:24:50,667 --> 00:24:53,467
Last time,
you looked so down.

423
00:24:53,600 --> 00:24:55,967
So, I got worried about you.

424
00:24:57,167 --> 00:24:58,600
I hope you're okay now.

425
00:24:58,733 --> 00:25:00,400
I miss seeing you smile.

426
00:25:02,767 --> 00:25:04,933
[CLEARS THROAT]

427
00:25:05,067 --> 00:25:07,167
Oh, you're invited too?

428
00:25:08,133 --> 00:25:11,000
Yes, they want my parents
to come, so I have to come too.

429
00:25:12,533 --> 00:25:15,400
It's a shame
that Jasmine can't come.

430
00:25:15,533 --> 00:25:17,733
But you'll be there, right?

431
00:25:17,867 --> 00:25:20,100
Then...

432
00:25:20,233 --> 00:25:22,867
it'll just be the two of us
at the party.

433
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:24,667
If that's okay with you.

434
00:25:26,667 --> 00:25:29,400
Xander, your hand.

435
00:25:32,667 --> 00:25:33,900
Oh, sorry.

436
00:25:36,467 --> 00:25:37,867
Is that a cell phone?

437
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:39,167
What?

438
00:25:39,300 --> 00:25:41,367
[INTENSE]

439
00:25:41,500 --> 00:25:43,100
That's a cell phone, right?

440
00:25:43,233 --> 00:25:44,167
Why is this here?

441
00:25:45,900 --> 00:25:47,867
That's Uncle Jobert's phone.

442
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:51,367
This is what we used
to record videos last time.

443
00:25:51,500 --> 00:25:57,100
[INTENSE MUSIC]

444
00:25:57,233 --> 00:25:59,500
Didn't I tell you already
not to call me for now?

445
00:25:59,633 --> 00:26:00,900
Because I'm watching
over Jasmine.

446
00:26:01,033 --> 00:26:02,467
We have a big problem.

447
00:26:02,600 --> 00:26:04,533
Edward got Jobert's phone

448
00:26:04,667 --> 00:26:06,400
and he's going to give it
to Marj.

449
00:26:06,533 --> 00:26:08,600
This belongs to Jobert.
Why do you have it?

450
00:26:08,767 --> 00:26:11,200
Oh, by the way, Marj,
I almost forgot.

451
00:26:11,333 --> 00:26:13,167
It's from Ashley.
You might want to have it.

452
00:26:13,300 --> 00:26:17,300
Paolo, if you don't act,
we'll both lose our families.

453
00:26:19,033 --> 00:26:20,667
Fix this, Paolo.

454
00:26:20,800 --> 00:26:23,400
Make sure it doesn't blow up.

455
00:26:23,533 --> 00:26:27,167
Because if it does,
our family will be destroyed.

456
00:26:27,300 --> 00:26:31,033
People always say that marriage
is about sacrifice.

457
00:26:31,167 --> 00:26:34,300
To be a good wife, they say
you always have to endure.

458
00:26:34,433 --> 00:26:35,767
Oh, my goodness!

459
00:26:35,900 --> 00:26:37,233
You shameless people!

460
00:26:37,367 --> 00:26:39,367
How could they do this to me?

461
00:26:39,500 --> 00:26:41,900
At home, you should be safe.

462
00:26:42,067 --> 00:26:45,200
Safe from chaos and safe
from lies.

463
00:26:45,333 --> 00:26:50,533
The foundation of this house
isn't stone but lies.
